RestTemplate: it is a template in spring boot that simplify communication between microservices
let say jobms needs to communicate with companyms to get details about company for given job

below is the simple example of how RestTemplate is used to get some information about company endpoint api
//if we want to include the details of company then we need to communicate to companyms
RestTemplate restTemplate = new RestTemplate();
Company company = restTemplate.getForObject("http://localhost:8081/companies/1", Company.class);//first parameter is request
// endpoint and second is response will be of which type
System.out.println("COMPANY" + company.getName());
System.out.println("COMPANY" + company.getId());

